  </metadata>
  <prompt>
    SprkChat's `accessToken: string` prop is the largest snapshot trap in the codebase (shared with PCFs, AnalysisWorkspace, SpaarkeAi). Drop the prop entirely. Require `authenticatedFetch: AuthenticatedFetchFn` and `getAccessToken: () => Promise<string>`. Internal hooks (useChatSession, useChatPlaybooks, useChatContextMapping) drop accessToken and use the passed authenticatedFetch. useSseStream calls getAccessToken() at stream-open.
  </prompt>
  <role>Senior React engineer + reviewer for the shared library API change.</role>
  <goal>
    ISprkChatProps requires authenticatedFetch + getAccessToken; accessToken is removed. All 3 internal hooks updated. useSseStream gets fresh token per-stream.
  </goal>
  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/SprkChat/types.ts (ISprkChatProps)</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/SprkChat/SprkChat.tsx</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/SprkChat/hooks/useChatSession.ts</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/SprkChat/hooks/useChatPlaybooks.ts</file>
