      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/hooks/useSseStream.ts</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>
  <steps>
    <step>Edit types.ts: ISprkChatProps — remove `accessToken: string`; add `authenticatedFetch: AuthenticatedFetchFn` and `getAccessToken: () => Promise&lt;string&gt;` as REQUIRED props. Update AuthenticatedFetchFn import from @spaarke/auth.</step>
    <step>Edit SprkChat.tsx — destructure new props; pass to internal hooks.</step>
    <step>Edit useChatSession.ts: remove accessToken option; require authenticatedFetch; replace all raw fetch + Bearer with authenticatedFetch.</step>
    <step>Same for useChatPlaybooks.ts and useChatContextMapping.ts.</step>
    <step>Edit useSseStream.ts: change signature so the caller passes getAccessToken instead of a token string. Call getAccessToken() right before opening the SSE stream (fresh token per stream).</step>
    <step>Find every caller of SprkChat in the repo (grep) — they will need updating in tasks 024-027. List them in this task's notes.</step>
    <step>Run tsc --noEmit on Spaarke.UI.Components — expect compile errors at SprkChat consumer sites (tracked in 024-027).</step>
  </steps>
