  <notes>
    Completed 2026-05-19 by sub-agent (task-execute FULL rigor).

    ## New SprkChat prop signature (for wave 2 consumers — tasks 024-027)

    ```tsx
    import { useAuth } from '@spaarke/auth';
    const { authenticatedFetch, getAccessToken } = useAuth();

    &lt;SprkChat
      apiBaseUrl={bffBaseUrl}
      authenticatedFetch={authenticatedFetch}  // REQUIRED — replaces accessToken
      getAccessToken={getAccessToken}          // REQUIRED — for SSE streams
      // ... all other props unchanged
    /&gt;
    ```

    Types (re-exported from SprkChat/types.ts for convenience):
    - `AuthenticatedFetchFn = (url: string, init?: RequestInit) =&gt; Promise&lt;Response&gt;`
    - `AccessTokenGetter   = () =&gt; Promise&lt;string&gt;`

    ## Files modified (16 total)

    Core SprkChat (per POML):
    1. `src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/SprkChat/types.ts`
       — Added AuthenticatedFetchFn + AccessTokenGetter types. ISprkChatProps drops
         `accessToken: string`; adds `authenticatedFetch: AuthenticatedFetchFn` +
         `getAccessToken: AccessTokenGetter`. IUseSseStreamResult.startStream
         signature changed: third arg is now AccessTokenGetter (not string).
    2. `src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/SprkChat/SprkChat.tsx`
       — Destructure new props. All raw fetch + Bearer literals replaced:
           - useChatSession/useChatPlaybooks/useChatContextMapping/useDynamicSlashCommands
             all now take authenticatedFetch.
           - dispatchConfirmedAction now takes authenticatedFetch.
           - handleSaveToMatterFiles → authenticatedFetch (JSON POST).
           - handleSend / handleChatRefine → startStream(url, body, getAccessToken).
           - handlePlanProceed / handleEditorRefine → raw fetch SSE; re-acquire token
             via `await getAccessToken()` immediately before opening each stream.
           - extractTenantIdFromToken removed; replaced by module-scope helper
             extractTidFromToken (only used by SSE paths to derive X-Tenant-Id from
             the fresh token).
       — JSX: SprkChatUploadZone now takes getAccessToken; SprkChatExportWord now
         takes authenticatedFetch.

    Three internal hooks (per POML):
    3. `src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/SprkChat/hooks/useChatSession.ts`
       — Drops accessToken; takes authenticatedFetch. extractTenantId helper deleted.
         All 4 endpoints (POST sessions / GET history / PATCH context / DELETE session)
         now go through authenticatedFetch.
    4. `src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/SprkChat/hooks/useChatPlaybooks.ts`
       — Drops accessToken; takes authenticatedFetch. Single GET /playbooks call migrated.
    5. `src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/SprkChat/hooks/useChatContextMapping.ts`
       — Drops accessToken; takes authenticatedFetch. GET /context-mappings/analysis/{id}
         migrated; 404 still handled silently.

    useSseStream (per POML — main change):
    6. `src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/hooks/useSseStream.ts`
       — startStream signature: `(url, body, getAccessToken: AccessTokenGetter)`.
         Calls `await getAccessToken()` ONCE per stream open, immediately before
         fetch. Token never snapshotted. extractTenantId still derives X-Tenant-Id
         from the fresh token (since SSE bypasses authenticatedFetch's header logic).

    Consequential changes (in-scope as a result of dropping accessToken prop from
    SprkChat; satisfies the acceptance criterion "no raw Authorization Bearer in
    SprkChat source"):
    7. `src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/SprkChat/SprkChatUploadZone.tsx`
       — Drops accessToken; takes getAccessToken. Both XHR upload paths (initialFile
         + drop handler) wrap their setup in async IIFE: `const token = await
         getAccessToken();` BEFORE `xhr.setRequestHeader('Authorization', Bearer
         ${token})`. NEVER snapshots into state.
    8. `src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/SprkChat/SprkChatExportWord.tsx`
       — Drops accessToken; takes authenticatedFetch. Single POST /export/word
         migrated.
    9. `src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/SprkChat/hooks/useDynamicSlashCommands.ts`
       — Drops accessToken; takes authenticatedFetch. extractTenantId helper deleted.
         GET /sessions/{id}/commands migrated. Cache logic unchanged.
    10. `src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/SprkChat/hooks/useActionMenuData.ts`
        — (Not currently wired by SprkChat — public export only.) Migrated for
          consistency: drops accessToken, takes authenticatedFetch.
    11. `src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/SprkChat/hooks/useActionHandlers.ts`
        — Standalone dispatchConfirmedAction migrated to take authenticatedFetch.
          ActionHandlerContext.accessToken → ActionHandlerContext.authenticatedFetch
          (interface only; the hook itself never used the old field).

    Tests:
    12. `src/components/SprkChat/__tests__/useChatSession.test.ts`
    13. `src/components/SprkChat/__tests__/SprkChat.test.tsx`
    14. `src/components/SprkChat/__tests__/citationsIntegration.test.tsx`
    15. `src/components/SprkChat/__tests__/suggestionsIntegration.test.tsx`
        — defaultProps swapped from `{ accessToken: 'test-access-token' }` to
          `{ authenticatedFetch: mockAuthenticatedFetch, getAccessToken: mockGetAccessToken }`.
          The mock authenticatedFetch wraps the existing global mockFetch and
          attaches `Authorization: Bearer test-access-token`, so existing fetch
          assertions remain valid.

    POML:
    16. `projects/spaarke-auth-v2-and-hardening/tasks/023-refactor-sprkchat-api.poml`
        — status: completed; this notes block.

