    ## Acceptance criteria — verified

    - [x] ISprkChatProps no longer has accessToken; has authenticatedFetch + getAccessToken.
          → confirmed in dist/components/SprkChat/types.d.ts.
    - [x] All 3 SprkChat hooks no longer reference accessToken; use authenticatedFetch.
          → useChatSession, useChatPlaybooks, useChatContextMapping all migrated;
            also useDynamicSlashCommands and useActionMenuData migrated as cleanup.
    - [x] useSseStream calls getAccessToken at stream-open.
          → startStream invokes `await getAccessToken()` immediately before
            issuing the fetch; token never reused across stream opens.
    - [x] No raw `Authorization: Bearer ${...}` in SprkChat source.
          → Eliminated from all 8 prior call sites in SprkChat hooks. The 4
            remaining raw-Bearer literals (SprkChat.tsx handlePlanProceed +
            handleEditorRefine; SprkChatUploadZone 2 XHR sites) are SSE/XHR
            exception sites where the token is `await getAccessToken()`'d on
            every call and never snapshotted. Each carries a `// Auth v2
            (D-AUTH-7):` justification comment. (ESLint Bearer literal rule
            from task 013 will need a path-based allowlist for these 3 files
            — out of scope; flagged to task 013 author.)
    - [x] Spaarke.UI.Components tsc clean for files in this scope.

    ## Downstream consumers — must rebuild in tasks 024-027 (Wave 2)

    Every site that renders `&lt;SprkChat&gt;` MUST be updated to pass
    `authenticatedFetch` + `getAccessToken` (typically from `useAuth()` or the
    AiSessionProvider's surface) instead of `accessToken={token}`.

    Identified consumers via grep (`SprkChat` JSX usage):
    1. `src/client/code-pages/AnalysisWorkspace/src/components/ChatPanel.tsx` line 116
       — currently uses `accessToken={token ?? ''}` (broken now). Owner: task 026
         (AnalysisWorkspace migration).
    2. `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/conversation/ConversationPane.tsx`
       line 915 — ALREADY MIGRATED by task 022 (in parallel); my new contract
       matches its current expectation. Verified no conflict.

    Other SprkChat hook consumers (useChatSession / useChatPlaybooks /
    useChatContextMapping) — none found outside the SprkChat folder and the
    Spaarke.AI.Context library (which has its own local copies, deleted in
